Date: Thu, 4 Dec 2025 14:34:32 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] Fix serialization of TDigestState

Calling `centroids()` also compresses the state, which can lead to fewer
items than what `centroidCount()` returned before compression.
That led to errors like:

    java.io.EOFException
    at org.elasticsearch.common.io.stream.InputStreamStreamInput.readByte(InputStreamStreamInput.java:59)
    at org.elasticsearch.common.io.stream.StreamInput.readInt(StreamInput.java:214)
    at org.elasticsearch.common.io.stream.StreamInput.readLong(StreamInput.java:256)
    at org.elasticsearch.common.io.stream.StreamInput.readDouble(StreamInput.java:523)
    at io.crate.execution.engine.aggregation.impl.TDigestState.read(TDigestState.java:92)

Because the receiving side received a `count` higher than the actual
mount of items sent.
